# Git Workflow

After completing each feature or meaningful chunk of work, create a git commit.

## Commit format

```
<type>: <short summary>

<bullet list of what was done>
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`

## What to include in the description

- List the key files/modules created or changed
- Mention architectural decisions if non-obvious (e.g. "Steam OpenID manually — Fastify-compatible")
- Note any migrations, build changes, or config fixes

## Example

```
feat: add AuthModule — Steam OpenID + JWT

- Steam OpenID flow implemented manually (no passport-steam, Fastify-compatible)
- JwtStrategy via passport-jwt, JwtAuthGuard with @Public() decorator
- @CurrentUser() param decorator
- UsersModule: createOrUpdate on Steam login
```

## When to commit

- After each module or feature is complete and TypeScript compiles clean
- After fixing a non-trivial bug
- After any migration or config change that affects the project setup
- At the end of every working session (update docs/plan.md first)
